The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Metro Recommends

 The film

 (Nandan III, 6.30 pm, January 8)

 Cine Club of The French Association along with Nandan present the screening of Je Ne Suis Pas La Pour Etre Aime, directed by Stephane Brize. The film revolves around a 51-year-old weary and lonely man who decides to join dance classes and meets a charming woman. 

 The music 

 (Calcutta School of Music, 7 pm, January 12)

 Legendary French cross-genre trumpeter Eric Truffaz will perform with his jazz quartet comprising Malcom Braff (piano), Christophe Chambet (bass) and Marc Erbetta (drums) for the Congo Square Jazz festival on January 19. For a better idea about Erik Truffaz and his music, attend a session organised by Jazz Listeners Forum. A screening of one of Truffazs 2003 performances will also be held. 

 The stage 

 (Rabindra Sadan amp; Sisir Mancha, January 12-30)

 The festival, organised by National School of Drama and Paschim Banga Natya Akademi, will be unveiled with noBody, a dance-theatre presentation by choreographer Sasha Waltz (Berlin), at Rabindra Sadan, 6.30 pm. A.G. Chidambara Rao Jambe from Mysore stages O Lear 

 On January 13 at Rabindra Sadan, 6 pm, while Ruwanthie de Chickera from Sri Lanka presents Checkpoint at Sisir Mancha, 3.30 pm. 

 On January 14, Kalakshetra (Chennai) will put up Rukmini Devi Arundales dance-theatre fusion Kannappar Kuravanji at Rabindra Sadan, 6 pm. Leszek Bzdyl from Poland presents Several Witty Observations at Sisir Mancha, 3.30 pm. 

 The display 

 (Gallery Rasa, 4 pm-8 pm, till January 14)

 The exhibits from traditional Japanese kilns have been organised by the consulate general of Japan in association with Gallery Rasa.




